# Go Backend Conventions

## Architecture
- Router: gorilla/mux with subrouters for `/auth`, `/admin`, `/api`
- Auth: JWT via golang-jwt/jwt/v4, middleware-based
- Storage: Redis (go-redis/redis/v8) — all data stored as JSON in Redis
- Docs: Swagger via swaggo/swag — update annotations when changing endpoints

## File Organization
```
backend-api/
├── auth/       # Auth handlers + middleware (JWT, CORS, admin)
├── common/     # Shared utils (Redis client, JWT config, response helpers)
├── deck/       # Deck, card, fact, stats handlers
├── media/      # File upload/download handlers
├── swagger/    # Swagger response type annotations
└── tests/      # unit/ and integration/ tests
```

## Coding Patterns

### Error Handling
```go
// Always return meaningful HTTP status codes and JSON error responses
if err != nil {
    common.SendErrorResponse(w, http.StatusInternalServerError, "Failed to fetch deck")
    return
}
```

### Middleware Chain
- Public routes: CorsMiddleware only
- Protected routes (`/api/*`): CorsMiddleware → JwtAuthMiddleware
- Admin routes (`/admin/api/*`): CorsMiddleware → AdminAuthMiddleware

### Redis Data Access
- Keys follow pattern: `user:{username}`, `deck:{deckId}`, etc.
- Always deserialize with proper null/type checks
- Use `common.Rdb` for Redis client access

### Swagger
- Add swagger annotations above every handler function
- Run `make swagger-local` or `make swagger-prod` to regenerate docs
- Swagger response types live in `swagger/` package

## Testing
- Unit tests in `tests/unit/`, integration tests in `tests/integration/`
- Integration tests require Redis service
- Run: `go test ./tests/unit/...` and `go test ./tests/integration/...`
